<topic id="marking-validation-errors">
  <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Text editing mode<indexterm>Validation errors</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Validation errors in Text mode</indexterm>
        <indexterm>XML documents<indexterm>Validation<indexterm>Text
          Mode</indexterm></indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Validating XML Documents<indexterm>Text Mode</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> can be configured to <xref
        href="automatic-validation.dita#automatic-validation">automatically validate
        documents</xref> while editing in the <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode, and actions are also
      available to <xref
        href="validation-actions-in-user-interface.dita#validation-actions-in-user-interface"
        >manually validate documents</xref> on-request.</p>
    <p>
      <fig id="figure-automatic-validation-oxygen" product="editor author developer">
        <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_continous_validation.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>
      <fig id="figure-automatic-validation-oxygenEclipse"
        product="editorEclipse authorEclipse developerEclipse">
        <title>Presenting Validation Errors in Text Mode</title>
        <image href="../img/ec_continous_validation.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p><b><u>Validation Marker Locations</u></b></p>
    <p>In <uicontrol>Text</uicontrol> mode, validation issues are marked in the following locations:<ul>
        <li>In the main editing pane, with the issue underlined in a color according to the type of
          issue.</li>
        <li>In the right-side vertical stripe, with a marker that is colored according to the type
          of issue.</li>
        <li>For attributes with detected issues, in the <xref
            href="attributes-panel.dita#attributes-panel"><uicontrol>Attributes</uicontrol>
            view</xref>, with the attribute and its value colored according to the type of
          issue.</li>
      </ul></p>
    <p><b><u>Validation Marker Colors</u></b></p>
    <p>The colors for each type of issue are as follows:<ul
        conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/ul-validation-markers">
        <li/>
      </ul><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-doc-pref-link"/><ph
        conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-annotations-pref-eclipse"/></p>
    <p><b><u>Validation Markers in the Right-Side Stripe</u></b></p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-stripe"/>
    <p><b><u>Hovering Over Validation Issues</u></b></p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-hovering"/>
    <p><b><u>Details About Validation Issues</u></b><ul>
        <li>Information about the issue is also displayed in the message area on the bottom of the
          editor panel (clicking the <uicontrol><image href="../img/Options16.png"/> Document
            checking options</uicontrol> button opens the <xref
            href="preferences-editor-document-checking.dita"><uicontrol>Document
              Checking</uicontrol> preferences page</xref> where you can configure some validation
            options<ph product="author developer editor"> (such as the colors used to present the
            validation issues). Some validation messages include an
            <?oxy_comment_start author="Steven" timestamp="20170927T101956+0300" comment="we have to edit this according to what is decided."?>icon
              (<image href="../img/StyleLink16.png"/>) that provides a link to a style guide or
            specification<?oxy_comment_end?></ph>.</li>
        <li product="author developer editor"><ph
            conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-status-messages"/></li>
        <li product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"><ph
            conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-status-messages-2"/></li>
        <li><ph conkeyref="reusables-editing-modes/p-validation-messages"/></li>
      </ul></p>
